docs.lead_paragraph: A meeting of the Central Republican Committee was held on Saturday evening at the Mercer-street House. C. C. LEIGH presided, and WILLIAM PEET, of the Eighth Ward, acted as Secretaries. Delegates from eighteen Wards were in attendance. Two delegations appearing from the Eleventh Ward, the subject was referred to a Committee on Credentials, with instructions to report at the next meeting.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Board of Councilmen had some important matters under consideration last evening. SMALL CARS ON THE HUDSON RIVER RAILROAD. Councilman WARDELL presented a petition, numerously signed by residents along the line of the Tenth and Eleventh avenues, asking that a great be given to Hunson River Railroad Company to run small cars upon their rails south of Fifty-ninth-street.
